Third-party reference skills vendored for calibration testing
=============================================================

Source repository: https://github.com/anthropics/skills
Source commit:     9d2f1ae187231d8199c64b5b762e1bdf2244733d
License:           Apache License 2.0

License verification
--------------------
Each vendored skill ships its own LICENSE.txt, and both were verified to be the
Apache License, Version 2.0 (January 2004) before copying:

    mcp-builder/LICENSE.txt     -> "Apache License, Version 2.0"
    webapp-testing/LICENSE.txt  -> "Apache License, Version 2.0"

The document skills in the upstream repo (docx, pdf, pptx, xlsx) were NOT
vendored: their LICENSE.txt is a proprietary "all rights reserved" Anthropic
license, not Apache-2.0.

Copied files
------------
Only each skill's SKILL.md and its own LICENSE.txt were copied, unmodified.
The upstream scripts/ and reference/ subfolders were intentionally not vendored
(skill-refine lints the SKILL.md only and does not resolve referenced files).

    skills/mcp-builder/SKILL.md       -> mcp-builder/SKILL.md
    skills/mcp-builder/LICENSE.txt    -> mcp-builder/LICENSE.txt
    skills/webapp-testing/SKILL.md    -> webapp-testing/SKILL.md
    skills/webapp-testing/LICENSE.txt -> webapp-testing/LICENSE.txt

Purpose
-------
These are read-only calibration fixtures: real, well-authored Agent Skills that
must score >= 8.0 with zero ERROR findings under skill-refine's `standard`
profile. mcp-builder additionally locks the empty-section regression fix.
